name: Jamie Primack
description: Comic Artist, Illustrator, Space Goth.
tweets: ...Overall, those are all minor nitpicks that simply added up over time, but nitpicks, nonetheless. Hellraiser was still very good, and I highly recommend it to anyone looking for a horror movie in October -- especially if you're looking to enjoy some fun body horror designs.

name: Jamie Primack
description: Comic Artist, Illustrator, Space Goth.
tweets: ...I think the movie should've focused on Voight. It would've allowed them to cut out a lot of exposition, cut out "middleman" characters, and would've allowed for some pretty fun human depravity juxtaposed with the depravity of the cenobites. But that's just my two cents...

name: Jamie Primack
description: Comic Artist, Illustrator, Space Goth.
tweets: ...I think the story suffered from being needlessly complicated. I understand that a movie like Hellraiser desires "cannon fodder" characters, but a more streamlined script would have no need for that. This might be an unpopular opinion, but...

name: Jamie Primack
description: Comic Artist, Illustrator, Space Goth.
tweets: ...there were things that held the movie back from being amazing. This might sound wild, but I thought the cenobites weren't gory enough. It's not that they need to be dripping blood and pus, but without that layer of "juice," the costumes look a bit rubbery sometimes. Also...

name: Jamie Primack
description: Comic Artist, Illustrator, Space Goth.
tweets: My thoughts on the new Hellraiser: overall, it was very good. Had great visuals and cinematography, and some creative body horror. The designs of the cenobites were unique and detailed, and apparently, Peter Mohrbacher did some of the costume designing, which is awesome), but...
